## 🗣️ Clarifying Questions & Answers

### 1. WHO — Actors

**Q: Who uses this system?**

| Actor | Role | Actions |
|-------|------|---------|
| **Student** | Consumer | Browse courses, enroll, watch content, take quizzes, get certificate |
| **Instructor** | Creator | Create courses, add modules/lessons/content, view analytics |
| **Admin** | Manager | Manage platform, approve courses (out of scope for interview) |

**For this interview:** Focus on Student and Instructor.

---

### 2. WHAT — Course Structure

**Q: What is the structure of a course?**

```
Course
├── title, description, price, instructor
├── Module 1: "Introduction"
│   ├── Lesson 1.1: "Welcome" (VIDEO)
│   ├── Lesson 1.2: "Setup" (TEXT)
│   └── Lesson 1.3: "Basics Quiz" (QUIZ)
├── Module 2: "Core Concepts"
│   ├── Lesson 2.1: "Variables" (VIDEO)
│   └── ...
└── Module 3: ...
```

**Key entities:**
- **Course** — Top level, has price and instructor
- **Module** — Section/chapter of course
- **Lesson** — Individual learning unit
- **Content** — The actual material (Video, Text, or Quiz)

---

### 3. Content Types

**Q: What types of content do we support?**

| Type | Description | Attributes |
|------|-------------|------------|
| **VIDEO** | Watch a video | url, duration |
| **TEXT** | Read an article | content (string) |
| **QUIZ** | Answer questions | questions, passing_score |

**Simplification:** No live sessions, PDFs, or assignments.

---

### 4. Pricing & Enrollment

**Q: Free or paid courses?**

- Each course has a **price** attribute
- If `price = 0` → **Free course** (enroll directly)
- If `price > 0` → **Paid course** (must purchase)
- Student can enroll in **multiple courses**
- Payment is simple (mark as paid, no actual gateway)

---

### 5. Quizzes

**Q: How do quizzes work?**

| Aspect | Decision |
|--------|----------|
| Question format | Multiple choice (1 correct answer) |
| Passing score | 70% (configurable per quiz) |
| Retries | Unlimited |
| Time limit | None |
| Quiz placement | At end of lesson or module |

**If student fails:**
- Can retry immediately
- Must pass all quizzes to get certificate

---

### 6. Progress Tracking

**Q: How is progress tracked?**

| Level | Tracking |
|-------|----------|
| **Lesson** | Completed / Not completed |
| **Quiz** | Best score, passed/failed |
| **Module** | % lessons completed |
| **Course** | % overall + quiz status |

**Completion formula:**
- All lessons in all modules marked as done ✅
- All quizzes passed (≥70%) ✅
- → Course complete → Certificate issued 🎓

---

### 7. Certificate

**Q: When and what is in the certificate?**

| Aspect | Decision |
|--------|----------|
| When issued | Automatically on course completion |
| Contains | Student name, Course name, Instructor name, Completion date |
| Downloadable | Yes (or just display) |

---

## ✅ Final Scope Summary

| Aspect | Decision |
|--------|----------|
| **Actors** | Student, Instructor |
| **Course Structure** | Course → Module → Lesson → Content |
| **Content Types** | Video, Text, Quiz |
| **Pricing** | Per course (can be 0 for free) |
